---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Bingos — 50-Point Bonus Plays & Training"
  description="Master Scrabble bingos with guides on probability, stems, training methods, prefixes, suffixes, and the best 7-letter racks. Free guides, no signup."
  keywords="scrabble bingo, 50 point bonus, seven letter words scrabble, bingo stems, scrabble bingo probability, how to get bingos, bingo training scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a bingo in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A bingo is when a player uses all 7 tiles from their rack in a single turn, earning a 50-point bonus on top of the word's regular score. Bingos are the fastest way to build a commanding lead and typically score 60-100+ total points per play." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often should you get bingos in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Expert players average 2-3 bingos per game. Intermediate players typically get 0-1. The key factors are vocabulary size, rack management (keeping bingo-friendly tiles), and recognizing anagram patterns quickly under time pressure." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best tiles to keep for a bingo?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The most productive bingo tiles are S, A, T, I, N, E, R, and blank tiles. The SATINE stem (AEINST) is the #1 six-letter bingo stem, producing over 200 valid 7-letter words. SATIRE (AEIRST) is #2 with 180+ words. Keeping 5-6 of these letters gives you the highest probability of drawing into a bingo." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 flex items-center gap-1">
      <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
      <span class="mx-1">›</span>
      <span class="text-gray-300">Bingos</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Bingos</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-6">
      The 50-point bonus that separates good players from great ones. These 15 guides cover bingo probability, 
      productive stems, training methods, common prefixes and suffixes, rack building, and the psychology of 
      spotting 7-letter words under pressure.
    </p>

    <!-- Stat Strip: Category Overview -->
    <div class="not-prose my-8 p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
        <div><p class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-400">15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Guides</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-400">+50</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bonus Points</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-400">2-3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Per Game (Expert)</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-400">200+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SATINE Anagrams</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Insight Callout -->
    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why Bingos Matter</p>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The difference between a player who bingos <span class="text-white font-medium">once every 5 games</span> and one who bingos <span class="text-white font-medium">twice per game</span> is worth 150+ points across a match. Tournament players don't get lucky — they systematically keep bingo-friendly tiles and practise anagram recognition daily.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Top Bingo Stem Pill Badges -->
    <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
      <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2">Top Bingo Tiles:</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">S</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">1 pt</span>
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">A</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">1 pt</span>
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">T</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">1 pt</span>
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">I</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">1 pt</span>
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">N</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">1 pt</span>
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">E</span><span class="text-purple-400 text-xs">1 pt</span>
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">?</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">Blank</span>
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Card #1: SATINE Stem -->
    <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-purple-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-950/30 to-indigo-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-purple-500/70">🏆 #1 Productive Stem</div>
      <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">S A T I N E</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-purple-300 font-semibold mb-3">200+ valid 7-letter words · 6-letter base + any 7th tile</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">SATINE (AEINST) is the single most productive 6-letter stem in Scrabble. These tiles are among the most common in the bag, giving you the highest statistical chance of drawing into a bingo. Example words: NASTIER, RETAINS, STAINER, STEARIN.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Card #2: SATIRE Stem -->
    <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-indigo-500/40 bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-950/30 to-purple-950/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-indigo-500/60">🥈 #2 Productive Stem</div>
      <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">S A T I R E</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-indigo-300 font-semibold mb-3">180+ valid 7-letter words · Swaps N for R from SATINE</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">SATIRE (AEIRST) is the second most productive stem. Just one letter different from SATINE — the R instead of N. Both stems share many bingo words and keeping either on your rack puts you in an excellent position. Example words: SATIRES, MAESTRI, PIRATES.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Section: Bingo Fundamentals -->
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Bingo Fundamentals</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Start here — understand what bingos are, the probability behind them, and which racks give you the best chance.</p>

    <div class="grid gap-4 not-prose">
      <a href="/blog/what-is-a-bingo/" class="block p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10 hover:border-green-400 transition-all group">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-900/50 border border-green-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-green-300 font-bold">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-green-400 transition-colors">What Is a Bingo?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The 50-point bonus explained — rules, scoring, and why bingos matter for competitive play.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/bingo-probability/" class="block p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10 hover:border-green-400 transition-all group">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-900/50 border border-green-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-green-300 font-bold">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-green-400 transition-colors">Bingo Probability</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The mathematics behind bingos — how rack composition affects your chances of playing all 7 tiles.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/best-bingo-racks/" class="block p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10 hover:border-green-400 transition-all group">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-900/50 border border-green-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-green-300 font-bold">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-green-400 transition-colors">Best Bingo Racks</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">The highest-probability 7-tile combinations — racks that almost guarantee a bingo exists.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Section: Stems & Strategy -->
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Stems & Strategy</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Build your rack intentionally — learn the stems, prefixes, and suffixes that turn 6 tiles into 7-letter bonus plays.</p>

    <div class="grid gap-4 not-prose">
      <a href="/blog/bingo-stem-strategy/" class="block p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10 hover:border-purple-400 transition-all group">
